rComments: Peter Sealy is one of my favourite instructors! He gives excellent feedback and will NOT make you feel bad for mistakes you make/things that you could change about your work. He really cares about his students and makes sure that you know your hard work is appreciated. He literally thanks his students for all the work they put in. I love him!!
One of great prof which deliver a clear and insprational lecture. He always make a short recap on the main point for the previous lecture and the lecture he give is clear in logic and make sense.
One of the best profs I've ever had.
One of the best professors I've had at UofT. He truly cares about his students and always makes sure the content he is teaching makes sense. Very organized in his lectures and approachable.

By far one of the most respected professors I have ever had! changed my perspective on architectural theory and history. I would definitely recommend his courses to other students because he is genuine and very helpful.
Fantastic prof - structures lectures well, really knows what he's talking about, and a genuinely nice guy.

Very clear presentation of subject and interesting approach to architecture. The only concern about this particular course is that your mark will be depended on your assigned TA. Got a terrible TA and resulted a low mark for an assignment.
